mponents/number-field#keyboard","content":"Keyboard"},"507":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-13","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/number-field#aria-and-labeling","content":"ARIA and labeling"},"508":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-14","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/number-field#best-practices","content":"Best practices"},"509":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-15","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#props","content":"The NumberField component accepts the following props:"},"510":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-16","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#basic","content":"Minimal usage with label, placeholder, and min/max."},"511":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-17","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#controlled","content":"Use `value` and `onChange` for controlled state."},"512":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-18","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#invalid","content":"Use `isInvalid` with `errorMessage` for validation feedback."},"513":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-19","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#disabled","content":"Use `isDisabled` to prevent input."},"514":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-20","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#hide-stepper","content":"Use `hideStepper` to show only the input without +/- buttons."},"515":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-21","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#value-scale","content":"Use `minValue`, `maxValue`, and `step` to set the allowed values. Steps are calculated from the minimum value."},"516":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-22","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#format-options-numbering-system","content":"By default, NumberField displays the value using the numbering system for the user's locale. Use the `formatOptions` prop to override the numbering system by setting the Unicode numbering system locale extension."},"517":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-23","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#keyboard","content":"When focus is in the input (and the field is not read-only), keyboard behavior follows common spinbutton-style conventions:"},"518":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-24","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#keyboard","content":"**Arrow Up** / **Arrow Down** (or **Up** / **Down**): increase or decrease by `step`"},"519":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-25","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#keyboard","content":"**Page Up** / **Page Down**: larger increase or decrease when supported"},"520":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-26","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#keyboard","content":"**Home** / **End**: jump to `minValue` or `maxValue` when those props are set"},"521":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-27","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#keyboard","content":"Stepper buttons are real buttons and follow standard button keyboard activation. Use &#x2A;*`incrementAriaLabel`*&#x2A; and &#x2A;*`decrementAriaLabel`** when the default labels are not enough in your locale or UI."},"522":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-28","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#aria-and-labeling","content":"The input is associated with the visible label and optional description and error content for assistive technologies."},"523":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-29","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#aria-and-labeling","content":"Invalid and required states are exposed to assistive technologies when you use `isInvalid`, `errorMessage`, and `isRequired`."},"524":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-30","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#aria-and-labeling","content":"Set &#x2A;*`isWheelDisabled`** if the value should not change when the user scrolls with a pointer wheel while the field is focused."},"525":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-31","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#best-practices","content":"Pair &#x2A;*`isInvalid`*&#x2A; with &#x2A;*`errorMessage`** so users get both visual and programmatic feedback."},"526":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-32","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#best-practices","content":"Remember valid steps start from &#x2A;*`minValue`**."},"527":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-33","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#best-practices","content":"Use &#x2A;*`isDisabled`*&#x2A; when the value cannot be changed; use &#x2A;*`isReadOnly`** when the value should be visible but not editable. Do not use them interchangeably."},"528":{"id":"/docs/components/number-field-34","page_id":"/docs/components/number-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/number-field#best-practices","content":"For currency or units, ensure &#x2A;*`formatOptions`** (and locale) match what users are allowed to type."},"529":{"id":"/docs/components/popover","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"page","content":"Popover","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover"},"530":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-0","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/popover","content":"The Popover component is an overlay element positioned relative to a trigger element."},"531":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-1","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#installation","content":"Installation"},"532":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-2","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#props","content":"Props"},"533":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-3","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#examples","content":"Examples"},"534":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-4","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#basic-usage","content":"Basic Usage"},"535":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-5","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#custom-anchor","content":"Custom Anchor"},"536":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-6","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#close-button-and-header","content":"Close Button and Header"},"537":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-7","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/popover#best-practices","content":"Best Practices"},"538":{"id":"/docs/components/popover-8","page_id":"/docs/components/popover","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/popover#basic-usage","content":"Use it with `<PopoverTrigger>`, which wraps both the popover content and an interactive\ntrigger element (for example, a `Button`)."},"539":{"id":"/do