","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Multiple series**: Shows all series that have a datum at the hovered X position in a single tooltip."},"1091":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Series matching**: Rows are built from `series` by matching `series[].id` to keys in `tooltipData.datumByKey` (from visx at the hovered X)."},"1092":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Value formatting**: You can supply a function to format each value; if you don't, the tooltip shows the point's `y` (or nothing when null). Use the formatter for custom data shapes."},"1093":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is intended for use inside chart components."},"1094":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#props","content":"The `Tooltip` component accepts the following props:"},"1095":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-14","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Default:** When `formatValue` is not provided, the tooltip uses a formatter that reads the data point’s `y` property (same as the chart's default Y accessor), converts it to a string, and returns an empty string for null. This is correct for the default `DataPoint` shape (`{ x, y }`)."},"1096":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-15","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Custom:** Pass `formatValue` to control display. The function receives the datum and returns a string. Use it to both extract and format (e.g. currency, percentage, custom units). For custom data point shapes (generic `TooltipProps<YourDatum>`), you must pass `formatValue` because the default only reads `y`."},"1097":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-16","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#single-series","content":"Basic tooltip with a single series and default formatting."},"1098":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-17","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#multiple-series","content":"Tooltip with multiple series; all series at the same X position are shown together."},"1099":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-18","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#arrow","content":"Use the `showArrow` prop to set whether the tooltip arrow is visible or not."},"1100":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"page","content":"TooltipDismissStrip","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip"},"1101":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","content":"Internal visx XYChart helper that closes the tooltip when the pointer enters a leading-edge strip over scroll-synced axis chrome"},"1102":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"Internal Component"},"1103":{